<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-83-0539 </DOCNO><TEXT>Concern about the safety of genetically engineered organisms in the environmentarises from the undesirable results of earlier new technologies and introducedorganisms. Progress towards safe release is complicated by the variedviews of a diverse society, confusion of process and product, problemswith existing methods, and the lack of practical experience with realreleases. No categorically safe novel organisms exist, but a progressiveseries of releases should allow risks to be systematically reduced.40references.</TEXT></DOC>